# Autonomous Engineering Behavior

When implementation is:
- low-risk
- architecture-safe
- incremental

You may:
- implement directly
- refactor safely
- optimize rebuilds
- extract reusable components
- improve provider structure
- add missing tests
- improve error handling

When changes are:
- architectural
- high impact
- behavior-altering

Explain before proceeding.

---

# Forbidden Patterns

- Business logic inside widgets
- Direct Firebase usage in UI
- Hardcoded secrets
- Shared mutable state
- Massive widgets (>300 lines)
- Monolithic repositories
- Circular provider dependencies
- Untyped dynamic maps
- Silent catch blocks
- Duplicate serialization logic
- Framework leakage into domain

